♪ Reality was written,
I put effort in my vision ♪

04:34.541 --> 04:35.774
♪ That's why I hustle so hard ♪

04:35.776 --> 04:37.609
♪ To be the best
that ever did it, oh! ♪

04:37.611 --> 04:40.679
I hope you're ready to make
your big announcement.

04:42.215 --> 04:44.716
Here we go.

04:44.718 --> 04:46.718
(clamoring)

04:53.593 --> 04:55.127
Hey, Becky.

04:55.129 --> 04:56.428
Hey, Anika.

04:56.430 --> 04:57.896
And Becky. Hey,
these are for today.

04:57.898 --> 04:59.564
Thanks.

04:59.566 --> 05:02.301
Okay, the designs for the jacket
line need approval by noon,

05:02.303 --> 05:03.802
and<i> The Tonight Show</i>
wants you to sing for...

05:03.804 --> 05:05.237
Pass.
Okay.

05:05.239 --> 05:06.805
Uh, the president
wants...

05:06.807 --> 05:07.806
Excuse you.

05:07.808 --> 05:09.107
I'm back here.

05:09.109 --> 05:10.475
Today is not
the day, Becky.

05:10.477 --> 05:12.911
Hear me?

05:12.913 --> 05:14.513
Everything go okay
at the doctor?

05:14.515 --> 05:16.515
Yeah, good. Come on.

05:16.517 --> 05:18.684
Okay. Well,
the president is asking

05:18.686 --> 05:20.485
that you'll attend
the China state dinner.

05:20.487 --> 05:22.120
Okay, tell Barack that...

05:22.122 --> 05:24.856
yes, but this is the last one
for the next few months.

05:24.858 --> 05:26.124
And after this press conference,

05:26.126 --> 05:27.926
I want you to cancel
all my meetings.

05:27.928 --> 05:28.860
All of them?

05:28.862 --> 05:30.329
Yes. And tell my sons

05:30.331 --> 05:32.164
to meet me at my house.

05:32.166 --> 05:35.767
I started selling drugs
when I was nine years old

05:35.769 --> 05:37.302
in Philadelphia.

05:37.304 --> 05:41.206
I did it to feed myself.

05:45.144 --> 05:47.713
But it was the music...

05:47.715 --> 05:50.282
that played in my head
that kept me alive

05:50.284 --> 05:52.851
when I thought
I was gonna get shot.

05:52.853 --> 05:54.953
And it was the melodies that...

05:54.955 --> 05:56.888
I dreamt about
that kept me warm

05:56.890 --> 05:59.991
while I was sleeping
in the streets.

05:59.993 --> 06:03.061
♪ Lyrically, I'm on point,
flowing double joint ♪

06:03.063 --> 06:04.830
♪ You just a little boy,
you a boy ♪

06:04.832 --> 06:06.465
♪ I'm a man, you
should be playing ♪

06:06.467 --> 06:08.400
(faint whooping)
♪ With your toys! ♪

06:08.402 --> 06:11.503
You see, music saved my life.

06:11.505 --> 06:12.738
Times have changed, though.

06:12.740 --> 06:14.306
The Internet has destroyed

06:14.308 --> 06:16.975
the musician's ability
to make money,

06:16.977 --> 06:20.679
because our work is downloaded
for free online.

06:20.681 --> 06:23.715
And now it's impossible
for the disenfranchised kids

06:23.717 --> 06:25.417
growing up
in the projects

06:25.419 --> 06:28.420
to overcome poverty
the way that I did.

06:28.422 --> 06:30.422
We are gonna change all of that.

06:30.424 --> 06:32.924
I am proud
to announce

06:32.926 --> 06:36.161
that Empire Entertainment
has filed to become

06:36.163 --> 06:40.132
a publicly traded company
on the New York Stock Exchange.

06:43.169 --> 06:45.003
Rita, did you bring the hummus?

06:45.005 --> 06:46.538
Hey, y'all.

06:46.540 --> 06:50.008
ANDRE: Jamal,
how's that friend of yours?

06:50.010 --> 06:53.078
Good. Why you flake on dinner
last Tuesday?

06:53.080 --> 06:55.013
Schedule was crazy.

06:55.015 --> 06:56.515
I mean, but you could've called
or something.

06:56.517 --> 06:58.016
Like, we cooked and everything.
That's so rude.

06:58.018 --> 06:59.151
I forgot.

07:03.122 --> 07:05.123
I'm glad you're all here.

07:05.125 --> 07:08.093
And get your big-ass feet
off my $40,000 table!

07:08.095 --> 07:09.828
I eat there!

07:14.567 --> 07:17.068
Your brother and I
have been working hard

07:17.070 --> 07:20.539
to turn Empire
into a publicly traded company.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.742
Now, part of us going public

07:23.744 --> 07:26.211
means ensuring a legacy
for this company,

07:26.213 --> 07:28.413
and right now it seems
none of you are prepared

07:28.415 --> 07:29.981
to take over after I'm gone.

07:31.417 --> 07:35.787
Now, it won't happen today,
nor tomorrow...

07:35.789 --> 07:39.391
but I<i> will</i> start
grooming someone soon.

07:39.393 --> 07:42.327
And it can only be
<i> one</i> of you.

07:42.329 --> 07:45.130
JAMAL: What is this,
we... we<i> King Lear</i> now?

07:45.132 --> 07:46.998
LUCIOUS: Call it what
you want, smart-ass,

07:47.000 --> 07:48.166
but over the next
several months...

07:48.168 --> 07:50.101
Wait, wait, wait.
What are you saying?

07:50.103 --> 07:52.170
We're all in competition to be
the future head of the company?

07:52.172 --> 07:56.808
In order for it to survive,
I need one of you Negroes

07:56.810 --> 07:59.344
to man up and lead it.

07:59.346 --> 08:03.381
And nothing or no one is going
to tear it down, hear me?

08:05.485 --> 08:07.819
COOKIE:
Thought I'd never see this day.

08:08.855 --> 08:11.423
Ink. Roll it.

08:11.425 --> 08:13.592
Last time I'm gonna be doing this.
(chuckles)

08:13.594 --> 08:15.594
(gate creaks)

08:15.596 --> 08:17.128
(laughs)

08:17.130 --> 08:19.264
(gate buzzes)

08:20.466 --> 08:22.100
(buzzing)

08:30.176 --> 08:33.411
Cookie's coming home.

08:40.720 --> 08:42.220
(distorted grunt)

08:42.222 --> 08:43.355
(grunting)

08:43.357 --> 08:45.023
You know how much money

08:45.025 --> 08:46.825
we're gonna make
off this boy?

08:46.827 --> 08:48.460
You sound like Don King, Dad.

08:48.462 --> 08:50.629
Don't say nothin' bad
about Dr. King.

08:50.631 --> 08:51.563
(laughing nearby)

08:51.565 --> 08:53.465
(continues laughing)

08:53.467 --> 08:56.635
Hey, Bunkie, give us a minute.

08:56.637 --> 09:00.372
What, right now?
Yeah, right now.

09:00.374 --> 09:02.874
I need to talk family business
with my son.

09:02.876 --> 09:06.077
♪ ♪

09:06.079 --> 09:08.980
You remember when
you were 11, sonny?

09:08.982 --> 09:10.749
(laughs): Dressing up
in a little suit,

09:10.751 --> 09:12.250
trying to run into the office,

09:12.252 --> 09:14.252
helping everybody,
answering phones.

09:14.254 --> 09:15.987
Even during my finals
at Penn, I was still

09:15.989 --> 09:17.255
coming back, doing
your accounting.

09:17.257 --> 09:19.491
Put your heart and guts
into this company.

09:19.493 --> 09:21.192
I mean, your
whole life is Empire.

09:21.194 --> 09:22.928
You went on
to grad school.

09:22.930 --> 09:24.696
Taught me a few things, too.

09:24.698 --> 09:25.897
Which makes me
the most qualified

09:25.899 --> 09:27.032
to run the company, Dad.

09:27.034 --> 09:28.433
And don't you think,

09:28.435 --> 09:30.535
since this is a
celebrity-driven brand,

09:30.537 --> 09:32.671
it should be run by a celebrity?
No, I don't.

09:32.673 --> 09:34.372
We're going public, Dre--
I got to think

09:34.374 --> 09:36.775
about all of this stuff.

09:36.777 --> 09:39.544
This successor talk have
anything to do with Cookie?

09:39.546 --> 09:42.047
What you talking about, Cookie? I haven't
spoken to her since she got out.

09:42.049 --> 09:44.749
I figured you had.
Cookie's out?

09:47.053 --> 09:48.920
It's your job to know.

09:48.922 --> 09:51.089
Slipped by me.
Slipped by you?

09:51.091 --> 09:55.260
Look, Money, you knew she
was gonna get out eventually.

09:55.262 --> 09:57.462
Why you starting
with Cookie?

09:57.464 --> 09:59.531
She ain't nothin'.

10:03.269 --> 10:05.270
From this moment forward,

10:05.272 --> 10:07.072
I want to know
everything she's doing.

10:07.074 --> 10:08.940
I mean everything.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.942
All right.

10:10.944 --> 10:13.445
Oh, hey, Money, I need 25.

10:13.447 --> 10:16.247
Oh, that's the last time, I swear.
I told you,

10:16.249 --> 10:17.916
if you ain't got the money,
don't make the bet.

10:17.918 --> 10:18.984
I want to know everything.

10:23.222 --> 10:25.290
♪ ♪

10:25.292 --> 10:27.225
He'd never pick me
anyway.

10:27.227 --> 10:28.893
Why?

10:28.895 --> 10:31.663
Way too much homophobia
in the black community.

10:31.665 --> 10:33.298
It's 2015.

10:33.300 --> 10:34.833
Nobody cares.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.835
There's football players
coming out.

10:36.837 --> 10:39.738
(sighs)

10:39.740 --> 10:41.906
Well, I don't want it
anyway-- so whatever.

10:43.976 --> 10:46.111
Then what do you want?

10:46.113 --> 10:48.647
You don't want to
release an album,

10:48.649 --> 10:50.915
you won't tour.

10:50.917 --> 10:53.118
Seen it my whole life.

10:53.120 --> 10:54.853
Hey, look at, look at my dad.

10:54.855 --> 10:57.288
That's a real artist.

10:57.290 --> 10:59.424
Well, he<i> was.</i>

10:59.426 --> 11:02.927
Now he's more concerned with
selling T-shirts and watches

11:02.929 --> 11:04.863
and whatever.

11:12.605 --> 11:14.372
(phone rings)

11:17.109 --> 11:18.677
Hello.

11:18.679 --> 11:19.811
COOKIE:
Let me in.

11:19.813 --> 11:20.912
Who's this?

11:24.550 --> 11:25.950
Let me in.

11:25.952 --> 11:28.319
Y'all better have
a elevator up in here.

11:28.321 --> 11:29.688
My feet hurt.

11:31.991 --> 11:34.526
Go in there
and tell your mama I love her,

11:34.528 --> 11:36.094
and don't come
back here crying.

11:43.736 --> 11:46.638
(indistinct,
overlapping chatter)

11:48.007 --> 11:50.675
When you coming home, Mama?

11:50.677 --> 11:52.911
I told you to stop
asking me that.

11:52.913 --> 11:55.180
Where's your father?

11:55.182 --> 11:58.850
He's not coming
to see you today.

11:58.852 --> 12:01.386
Yeah, okay.

12:01.388 --> 12:04.689
How you doing in school,
little man?

12:04.691 --> 12:07.058
My friends are picking on me.

12:07.060 --> 12:08.526
Bashir stole my lunch.

12:08.528 --> 12:10.161
I'm afraid to tell Dad.

12:10.163 --> 12:11.563
He'll tell me to fight.

12:11.565 --> 12:13.998
Listen to me.

12:15.101 --> 12:17.001
You different.

12:17.003 --> 12:18.770
Okay?

12:18.772 --> 12:21.940
It's only something
Mama knows, but

12:21.942 --> 12:25.777
it's gonna make life hard
for you sometimes.

12:25.779 --> 12:28.780
But I want you to always
remember I got you.

12:28.782 --> 12:30.882
You hear me?

12:30.884 --> 12:33.351
Come here.

12:34.854 --> 12:36.788
I got you.

12:36.790 --> 12:39.190
Okay?

12:39.192 --> 12:40.592
Hey, she's coming.

12:40.594 --> 12:43.361
Oh, my God. How?

12:43.363 --> 12:44.796
I don't know.

12:44.798 --> 12:46.898
Did you tell her
about us?

12:46.900 --> 12:48.867
Um...
And this.

12:48.869 --> 12:51.336
Take that.

12:54.073 --> 12:56.274
(doors clack open)

12:57.476 --> 12:59.878
Oh.

12:59.880 --> 13:02.781
(sighs)

13:02.783 --> 13:05.283
Mmm.

13:08.788 --> 13:11.990
For a queen, you sure
do keep a messy place.

13:11.992 --> 13:14.759
What you need is a
good maid up in here.

13:14.761 --> 13:16.995
You cooking chicken?

13:16.997 --> 13:18.997
Oh, yeah, yeah. Um...
Did you fry it?

13:18.999 --> 13:21.332
No, it's stewed, but it's
here this way.  Stewed?

13:21.334 --> 13:23.468
Might be a little spicy for you.
Stewed chicken.

13:23.470 --> 13:25.570
It's the way
we like it, so, you know.

13:25.572 --> 13:27.939
Uh, who is this?
Hi.

13:27.941 --> 13:29.474
Oh. That's Michael.
Michael.

13:29.476 --> 13:31.609
Uh, we're sort of
living together.

13:31.611 --> 13:33.845
Uh, look, Mommy,
I know you're hungry.

13:33.847 --> 13:35.780
Oh. Oh, honey,
you didn't tell me

13:35.782 --> 13:37.649
you was dating
a little Mexican.

13:37.651 --> 13:39.150
Look at her.
She's adorable.

13:39.152 --> 13:40.852
Yeah, I said "a little
Mexican." (Michael laughs)

13:40.854 --> 13:43.488
You need to get La Cucaracha
to clean up around here a bit.

13:43.490 --> 13:44.923
Uh, what are
you wearing?

13:44.925 --> 13:46.324
(sighs)
What I got locked up in.

13:46.326 --> 13:47.992
Well, we gonna
change that real quick.

13:47.994 --> 13:49.627
And why didn't you call me?
I would have picked you up.

13:49.629 --> 13:51.830
I just got out.

13:51.832 --> 13:53.464
Good behavior.

13:53.466 --> 13:55.466
All right, so,

13:55.468 --> 13:57.068
what are you gonna do now?

13:59.338 --> 14:01.873
I'm here to get what's mine.

14:06.278 --> 14:07.946
BECKY:
<i> You can't just go in there.</i>

14:07.948 --> 14:10.415
Get your ass
out of the way.

14:41.680 --> 14:43.581
(door opens)

14:43.583 --> 14:46.651
Ladies and gentlemen,
the queen has returned.

14:50.823 --> 14:53.191
Wow.

14:53.193 --> 14:57.996
17 years later, and
you are still beautiful.

15:00.599 --> 15:02.033
So, when did you get out?

15:02.035 --> 15:03.601
Two days ago.

15:03.603 --> 15:07.338
You really, uh...

15:07.340 --> 15:10.074
It was your sacrifice that made
a lot of this possible.

15:12.745 --> 15:15.480
I can't imagine what
you've been through, Cookie.

15:16.949 --> 15:18.516
But you've got to know

15:18.518 --> 15:21.586
you're not the only one
that suffered in this.

15:21.588 --> 15:24.756
You forgot about me the second
you divorced me in there.

15:25.858 --> 15:27.859
You still owe me what's mine.

15:27.861 --> 15:29.394
What are you talking about?

15:29.396 --> 15:31.729
Half of this company.

15:31.731 --> 15:34.432
It was my $400,000
that started this bitch.

15:34.434 --> 15:35.867
You know it,

15:35.869 --> 15:37.568
and I know it.

15:37.570 --> 15:39.370
Did 17 hard years
for that money,

15:39.372 --> 15:41.773
and I want half my company back.

15:41.775 --> 15:45.376
(laughing): I'm sorry, Cookie,
but it don't work like that.

15:45.378 --> 15:47.612
It don't work like what, honey?

15:47.614 --> 15:51.149
This company isn't the company
that we started 17 years ago.

15:51.151 --> 15:52.951
As a matter of fact,

15:52.953 --> 15:55.820
I control maybe ten percent
of this damn thing.

15:55.822 --> 15:59.123
I've got a board of directors,
quarterly reports, SEC filings.

15:59.125 --> 16:00.825
